OL,6,FMorning Live at 9.15am has been
OL,7,Fsuccessful so I'd be surprised if it
OL,8,Fwas dropped. But clearly fewer
OL,9,Fprogrammes would need to be
OL,10,Fcommissioned to cover the morning
OL,11,Fschedule.
OL,13,FIs this a stealth cut or a
OL,14,Fredistribution of resources?
OL,16,FThere'd also need to be a change in
OL,17,Fafternoon commissioning.
OL,19,FExtending the two main news
OL,20,Fprogrammes carries attractions. It
OL,21,Fcould be a cost-effective way to
OL,22,Fbuild on success.
OL,3,CChanges for BBC Breakfast and BBC
OL,4,CNews at One?
